Portions of the apply-patch parser/applier (crates/bharatcode-apply-patch:
parser.rs, streaming_parser.rs, seek_sequence.rs, and the compute/apply
replacement core) are derived from the codex-apply-patch crate. The vendored
subset depends only on thiserror; Codex's Ratatui (MIT) attribution does not
apply here because the apply-patch crate does not pull Ratatui.

Portions of the in-process Linux exec sandbox (crates/bharatcode-linux-sandbox:
the set_no_new_privs, Landlock filesystem ruleset, and Restricted-mode network
seccomp primitives in src/lib.rs) are derived from Codex's codex-linux-sandbox
crate (linux-sandbox/src/landlock.rs). The vendored subset depends only on
thiserror (all targets) plus landlock and seccompiler (Linux only); Codex's
bubblewrap launcher, proxy-routed network mode, and seatbelt/windows backends
are not included.
